sp. n. paratype, slide No. RH15321 12 
<taxonomicName id="DC55D91FE9485E4203268981D06DA174" genus="L." lsidName="L. solivaga" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="solivaga">L. solivaga</taxonomicName>
sp. n. paratype, slide No. RH16484 13 
<taxonomicName id="038EE10B2DB00F495260FFF8C9931919" genus="L." lsidName="L. muscosalis" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="muscosalis">L. muscosalis</taxonomicName>
, slide No. RH15249. Scale bars: 1.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="102BE43C0573280A29BC6D0F5B965021" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Female genitalia (Figs 14-16). Eighth tergite with anterior margin shallowly concave medially; eighth sternite narrow, membranous medially. Apophyses anteriores longer than apophyses posteriores, usually expanded basally. Antrum weakly sclerotized. Ductus bursae usually S shaped distally, with longitudinal sclerotized ridges. Corpus bursae ovate; signa two, ovate, with strongly sclerotized ridge medially.</paragraph>
